":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will fatal.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"A model builder is a more generic type of model. A model can be quite static,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"thus, you have to be quite careful to have a model work with dynamic inputs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You cannot use reshape, or anything that can generate fixed tensor outputs from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a fixed inputs.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"s:3NNC12ModelBuilderC","modules":[{"name":"NNC"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"}],"title":"ModelBuilder","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/nnc\/modelbuilder"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/NNC/ModelBuilder/compile